        <div class="body">
            <p>That looks like eAccelerator doesn't catch exception if it's actually inherited from the specified class (Zend_Search_Lucene code tries to catch Zend_Search_Exception exception object when it's actually Zend_Search_Lucene_Exception) .</p>

<p>It doesn't matter which type of exception to catch, so changing caught exception type to Zend_Search_Lucene_Exception should resolve the problem.
But it's still a bug in eAccelerator.</p>

